<H2><U>
Native American Legends About Turtles
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.leveillee.net/creationstory.htm
">Indian Turtle Island Legend</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.uwosh.edu/coehs/cmagproject/ethnomath/legend/legend9.htm
">The Turtle and the Flood</a>:</b> <B><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/AbenakiCreationStoryandTheImportanceofDreaming-Abenaki.html
">Abenaki Creation Story</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://henryhahn.net/myths/lenapecreation.html
">Turtle Island</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://web.archive.org/web/20071110053113/http://www.l-spioneers.org/mmeylin/teams/cobra/SS/1stAmericans/Len.creation.html
">Lenape Creation</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://dept.cs.williams.edu/~lindsey/myths/myths_12.html
">Iroquois Creation Myth</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Woodland Indian stories about the earth being placed on the back of a turtle.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/How-Glooskap-made-his-Uncle-Mikchich-the-Turtle-Micmac.html
">Glooskap and the Turtle Story</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.indians.org/welker/mikcheec.htm
">The Changing of Mikcheech</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://umaine.edu/folklife/publications/online-publications/northeast-folklore/kluskap-tales-from-the-malecite/#Turtle
">Kluskap and his Uncle Turtle</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The adventures of Glooskap and his uncle the Turtle.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/TurtleGetsaShell-Anishnabe.html
">Turtle Gets a Shell</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.mpm.edu/wirp/ICW-141.html#tortoise
">A House for Tortoise</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Chippewa and Ottawa Indian legends about how turtles got their shells.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.uwosh.edu/coehs/cmagproject/ethnomath/legend/legend13.htm
">How the Turtle Flew South for the Winter</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Oneida legend about Turtle's impatience getting him into trouble.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.mpm.edu/wirp/ICW-137.html#NAME
">Turtle Goes to War</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Potawatomi legend about the turtle people trying to attack a human village.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.museum.state.il.us/muslink/nat_amer/post/htmls/popups/be_turtle.html
">The Painted Turtle Legend</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Illinois Indian story about a woman who married a turtle.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.colorado.edu/csilw/arapahoproject/traditional/creation.htm
">Arapaho Deluge Story</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.markville.ss.yrdsb.edu.on.ca/history/religion/abmyth3.html
">The Creation of the World</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Arapaho and Gros Ventre myths about Turtle the Earth-Diver bringing earth for the new world.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://pyramidmesa.com/caddo2.htm
">The Voice, the Flood and the Turtle</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Caddo myth about Turtle saving the world from four deadly giants.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.accessgenealogy.com/scripts/data/database.cgi?file=Data&report=SingleArticle&ArticleID=0024292
">Coyote And Turtle Run A Race</A>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Caddo legend about Turtle using his wits to win a race with Coyote.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><b><A HREF="
http://www.accessgenealogy.com/scripts/data/database.cgi?file=Data&report=SingleArticle&ArticleID=0024272
">The Turtle Who Carried The People Away</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Caddo legend about a turtle who punished people who accidentally disrespected it.
<BR>

<H2><U>
Recommended Books of Turtle Stories from Native American Myth and Legend
</u><BR><font size=2>Our organization earns a commission from any book bought through these links</font>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0142404667/natilangofthe-20
">Turtle's Race With Beaver</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Lively children's book illustrating a Seneca legend about Beaver being outwitted by the slower but cleverer Turtle.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1555661904/natilangofthe-20
">A World of Turtles</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Collection of turtle folklore from all over the world, including ten different Native American tribes.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0152053743/natilangofthe-20
">Jabuti the Tortoise: A Trickster Tale from the Amazon</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Colorful picture book for kids telling the story of the trickster turtle Jabuti from the Tupi-Guarani tribes of Brazil.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0921827407/natilangofthe-20
">How the Turtle Got Its Shell</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A nice retelling of a Chippewa Indian legend about Nanabosho's gift to Turtle.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/053109524X/natilangofthe-20
">Remaking The Earth</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Picture book based on Blackfoot and Arapaho myths about the creation of Turtle Island.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0803717288/natilangofthe-20
">How Turtle's Back Was Cracked</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Picture book based on a Cherokee legend about Turtle paying the price for his bragging.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0452276500/natilangofthe-20
">Spirits of the Earth: A Guide to Native American Nature Symbols, Stories, and Ceremonies</A></B>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Book by a Karuk elder about the meaning of Indian animal spirits, including a chapter on turtles.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1555911277/natilangofthe-20
">Native American Animal Stories</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Great collection of tales about American Indian turtles and other animals, told by Abenaki storyteller Joseph Bruchac. 
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0689822332/natilangofthe-20
">Turtle Island: Tales of the Algonquian Nations</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Collection of legends from the Algonquian tribes.
<BR>




